text: Bak kut teh had barely any taste, ingredients were a bit sad, what you see in the pics are as is, no hidden ingredients underneath. Curry was decent. Overall I'll blacklist this place and won't return

Hi guys, let me be the 1st person to review this store. It is a new store and the food tastes average and the bat ku teh costs $9.5 with rice which is bloody expensive. Guess what's the best part, it provides only innoki mushroom, 3 slices of pork belly and 2 mini meat when i take away. Absolutely garbage and trash! Highly recommend u to try the bat ku teh at the top with air-conditioned. This is the 1st time and last trying.

I ordered two portions of pig's trotters in vinegar and salted fish belly in pot
As an Ipohian, I can give full marks to these two portions. I added two bowls of rice.
The food in the coffee shop tastes like my grandma's home. The food is delicious and really has the taste of home.
First time eating here, rarely see Malaysia style food. I think it tastes good, but the place is too hot and not ventilated. I kept sweating while eating, so I only give it 4 stars.
